  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On page 1 of the manuscript, there is a letter by Maria Weston Chapman to Caroline Weston. She discusses arrangements for an anti-slavery fair.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On page 3, there is a separate letter from John Levy to Maria Weston Chapman, dated March 27, 1843, Lowell, [Mass.]. Levy says that Chapel Hall can be obtained for an anti-slavery fair. He asks about the notice to be published.</subfield>
